# Package Import Rules

## Description

Rules for importing packages in the 77-projects monorepo.

## Pattern

\*_/_.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}

## Instructions

1. Always use the package name directly when importing, not direct paths to node_modules:

   ```javascript
   // CORRECT
   const { someModule } = require("package-name/path/to/module");
   import { someModule } from "package-name/path/to/module";

   // INCORRECT
   const {
     someModule,
   } = require("../../node_modules/package-name/path/to/module");
   import { someModule } from "../../node_modules/package-name/path/to/module";
   ```

2. For packages within the monorepo, ensure they are properly defined in the package.json before importing them.

3. The pnpm workspace configuration handles resolving imports between packages.

## Examples

### Correct

```javascript
import { Button } from "77-projects/components";
const { utils } = require("77-projects/core/utils");
```

### Incorrect

```javascript
import { Button } from "../../node_modules/77-projects/components";
const { utils } = require("../../node_modules/77-projects/core/utils");
```
